---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About Littleton | Town of Littleton, NH" description="Learn about the Town of Littleton, New Hampshire — a welcoming community nestled in the White Mountains region with small-town charm and natural beauty.">

  <!-- Page Hero -->
  <section aria-labelledby="hero-heading" class="bg-light-blue py-16 text-center">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-8">
      <h2 id="hero-heading" class="text-4xl font-bold text-navy mb-4">About Littleton</h2>
      <p class="text-body-text text-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        A welcoming community nestled in the heart of New Hampshire's White Mountains region, where small-town charm meets natural beauty.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Town Story -->
  <section aria-labelledby="story-section-heading" class="bg-white py-16">
    <h2 id="story-section-heading" class="sr-only">Town Story and Quick Facts</h2>
    <div class="story-grid">
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-6">Our Story</h3>
        <p class="text-body-text mb-4">
          Littleton, New Hampshire was chartered in 1764, making it one of the oldest towns in the White Mountains region. Situated along the banks of the Ammonoosuc River, our community has grown from a small colonial settlement into a thriving town that serves as the gateway to the majestic White Mountains.
        </p>
        <p class="text-body-text mb-4">
          Our historic Main Street, lined with locally-owned shops, restaurants, and galleries, captures the essence of New England charm. The town has carefully preserved its architectural heritage while embracing modern amenities, creating a unique blend of past and present that residents and visitors alike appreciate.
        </p>
        <p class="text-body-text">
          With a population of approximately 6,000 residents, Littleton offers the warmth and connection of a small community while providing access to exceptional outdoor recreation, cultural events, and natural beauty. From world-class skiing and hiking to peaceful riverside walks, our town is a haven for those who love the outdoors.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-6">Quick Facts</h3>
        <dl class="space-y-4">
          <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-mid-blue pb-2">
            <dt class="font-semibold text-navy">Founded</dt>
            <dd class="text-body-text">1764</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-mid-blue pb-2">
            <dt class="font-semibold text-navy">Population</dt>
            <dd class="text-body-text">~6,000</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-mid-blue pb-2">
            <dt class="font-semibold text-navy">County</dt>
            <dd class="text-body-text">Grafton County</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-mid-blue pb-2">
            <dt class="font-semibold text-navy">Region</dt>
            <dd class="text-body-text">White Mountains</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-mid-blue pb-2">
            <dt class="font-semibold text-navy">Elevation</dt>
            <dd class="text-body-text">748 feet</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-mid-blue pb-2">
            <dt class="font-semibold text-navy">Area</dt>
            <dd class="text-body-text">52.4 square miles</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-mid-blue pb-2">
            <dt class="font-semibold text-navy">Congressional District</dt>
            <dd class="text-body-text">NH-2</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between">
            <dt class="font-semibold text-navy">Annual Snowfall</dt>
            <dd class="text-body-text">~90 inches</dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Community Values -->
  <section aria-labelledby="values-heading" class="bg-light-blue py-16">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-8">
      <h2 id="values-heading" class="text-3xl font-bold text-navy text-center mb-10">What Makes Littleton Special</h2>
      <div class="values-grid">

        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-6 border-t-4 border-mid-blue">
          <svg aria-hidden="true" class="w-12 h-12 text-mid-blue mb-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 3v4M3 5h4M6 17v4m-2-2h4m5-16l2.286 6.857L21 12l-5.714 2.143L13 21l-2.286-6.857L5 12l5.714-2.143L13 3z" />
          </svg>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy mb-3">Natural Beauty</h3>
          <p class="text-body-text">
            Surrounded by the stunning White Mountains and Franconia Notch, Littleton offers endless opportunities for hiking, skiing, and exploring pristine rivers and forests throughout all four seasons.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-6 border-t-4 border-mid-blue">
          <svg aria-hidden="true" class="w-12 h-12 text-mid-blue mb-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 00-5.356-1.857M17 20H7m10 0v-2c0-.656-.126-1.283-.356-1.857M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 015.356-1.857M7 20v-2c0-.656.126-1.283.356-1.857m0 0a5.002 5.002 0 019.288 0M15 7a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm6 3a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0zM7 10a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0z" />
          </svg>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy mb-3">Vibrant Community</h3>
          <p class="text-body-text">
            Our historic Main Street is home to locally-owned businesses, a beloved farmers market, and year-round community events that bring neighbors together and celebrate our shared heritage.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-6 border-t-4 border-mid-blue">
          <svg aria-hidden="true" class="w-12 h-12 text-mid-blue mb-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 21V5a2 2 0 00-2-2H7a2 2 0 00-2 2v16m14 0h2m-2 0h-5m-9 0H3m2 0h5M9 7h1m-1 4h1m4-4h1m-1 4h1m-5 10v-5a1 1 0 011-1h2a1 1 0 011 1v5m-4 0h4" />
          </svg>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy mb-3">Rich History</h3>
          <p class="text-body-text mb-4">
            Chartered in 1764, Littleton boasts the historic Littleton Grist Mill, a beautifully preserved downtown, and deep New England heritage that connects us to generations past.
          </p>
          <a
            href="/about/history"
            class="text-navy font-semibold hover:underline focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-gold focus:ring-offset-2 rounded"
          >
            Explore Our History <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
          </a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Town Leadership -->
  <section aria-labelledby="leadership-heading" class="bg-white py-16">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-8 text-center">
      <h2 id="leadership-heading" class="text-3xl font-bold text-navy mb-6">Town Leadership</h2>
      <p class="text-body-text max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-8">
        Littleton is served by an elected Selectboard, Town Clerk, Town Treasurer, and Town Moderator, supported by a dedicated team of department heads and staff.
      </p>
      <a
        href="/about/officials"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-navy text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:opacity-90 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-navy focus:ring-offset-2"
      >
        View Full Officials &amp; Staff Directory <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Visit Littleton CTA -->
  <section aria-labelledby="visit-heading" class="bg-navy py-16 text-center">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-8">
      <h2 id="visit-heading" class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Plan Your Visit</h2>
      <p class="text-white text-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-8">
        Whether you're exploring the White Mountains, discovering our historic Main Street, or considering making Littleton your home, we welcome you to experience all that our community has to offer.
      </p>
      <div class="flex justify-center gap-4 flex-wrap">
        <a
          href="/calendar"
          class="inline-block bg-gold text-navy font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:opacity-90 transition-opacity focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-white focus:ring-offset-2"
        >
          View Town Calendar
        </a>
        <a
          href="/contact"
          class="inline-block bg-white text-navy font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:opacity-90 transition-opacity focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-gold focus:ring-offset-2"
        >
          Contact Town Hall
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .sr-only {
    position: absolute;
    width: 1px;
    height: 1px;
    padding: 0;
    margin: -1px;
    overflow: hidden;
    clip: rect(0, 0, 0, 0);
    white-space: nowrap;
    border-width: 0;
  }

  .story-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 64px;
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 32px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .story-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }

  .values-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 24px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .values-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }

  .leadership-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 24px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .leadership-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>